.TH hsh 1 "22nd August 2025" "1.0" "hsh man page"
.SH NAME
hsh \- a simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B #include "shell.h"
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hsh
is a simple command language interpreter that reads commands from standard
input or a file and executes them. It mimics some of the functionality of
the standard UNIX shell.
.PP
In interactive mode,
.B hsh
displays a prompt ($) and waits for a command line to be entered.
.PP
In non-interactive mode,
.B hsh
executes commands from a specified file. It does not display a prompt.
.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
The following built-in commands are available:
.TP
.B exit
Exits the shell, optionally with a status of
.I n.
.TP
.B env
Prints the current environment to standard output.
.TP
.B ls
List directory contents
.TP
.B help
Provides information about the shell and its built-in commands.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B PATH
The shell uses the
.B PATH
environment variable to find executable commands. The directories in
.B PATH
are searched in the order they appear.
.TP
.B PROMPT
The shell uses the
.B PROMPT
environment variable to customize the prompt string.
.SH EXAMPLES
The following is an example of a echo command:
.PP
.nf
echo "hello, world"
.fi
.PP
This would produce the output:
.PP
.nf
hello, world
.fi
